
done in 1.4.0:

-remove RTT from dir ptr drawing (useful for dirPrediction)
-filled world
-hit area
-dir ptr
-click to enable mouse mode
-lock should be better visible (use classic way)
-weapon modifiers at left bottom of hud
-keep altPower (not needed for bloods, but useful for ndh)
-fix segfault on map fishtank.xp (memory allocation for
 hud radar walls was broken if map width was bigger than
 height)
-Remove Lock, Modifiers and Fuel from ExtHUD, since they are
 on the HUD. Would make additional room for stats in ExtHUD.
-Some confusion with radarScale and hudRadarScale. They seem to
 have different effect in current bpc-x11 and older (ng-)clients.
 Scaling seems to be doubled in current bpc-x11. (1.3.8alpha2)
 EXPLANATION: in bp client, hudRadar scale is invariant
 of scaleFactor.
-option hudRadarDotSize seems not working - removed because
 server sends the dot sizes to client
-Move the drawing of the hudWallRadar-basewarning to the normal
 hudRadar (the flashing dot).
 That makes it visible even if the hudWallRadar is toggled off.
-scorelist should be toggleable. could begin just below the last line of 
 maxMessages and probably extend upto the start of the servermessages
 at the bottom (maxMessages)
-use hudradarothercolor for any non-enemy, allies etc.
-extend the drawing of the dirPointer to also draw the small
 frontside line of the ship (move that from Mara's shipShapeHack to
 the dirPointer code).  It helps to see the shipdirection better
 (especially on small display).  Will also draw it if the ship is
 cloaked or phased, which is nice and the shipShapeHack does not do.
-problem: KP_enter not available on some laptops - solution:
 use mouse button to enter mouse control mode, use Escape to exit;
 remove keyPointerControl option
-buttons to toggle ext hud radar (walls, bases on radar), score list,
 "ext hud", messages
-meta2 ip updated
-The color config supports the text "off". It's more self explaining than
 using color 0 (black) for "don't draw".
-don't send team talkmacros if teamplay is off
-don't clear talk window on Escape
-make ball and cover indicator circles on ship bigger
-don't put radar walls into recordings, they use too much space and
 clutter the view
-have abbreviated statsnames on ExtHUD, while still sending
 the former unabbreviated stats to stdout (if selected).
-make hudScale independent of scaleFactor
-up to 48 colors in use for color options (16 xpilot colors + 32 "color code" colors)
-recordings on poly maps record the style colors of polygons and edges
-don't use xf86misc to check emulate3buttons due to problems on unstable debian

done prior to 1.4.0:

