- Problems with local 4.5.4 server running newdarkhell.xp.
  After a while (maybe 10-15 mins) it stalls with
  bpc-x11-1.3.8alpha: ERROR: send (1): (Connection refused)
  bpc-x11-1.3.8alpha: ERROR: recv (1): (Connection refused)
  bpc-x11-1.3.8alpha: WARNING: No response from server
  _Server_ seemed to die/freeze. Did not occur again after the
  segfault (wrong map size allocation) was fixed.

- Scorelist could start one line higher and be also pushed down
  when the "Quit | Menu" buttons are displayed (like messages).

- Servermessages could be indented by the width of scorelist
  if window is wide enough to still display the longest
  (possible) message.
  That would prevent painting the scorelist over the servermessages
  if scorelist is very long (for example fishtank map).
  Playermessages could be indented in the same way, so that
  the scorelist could start at the top, left of the
  playermessages.



- Default of hudRadarWallColor (=15) is invisible on my display
  (too dark).  Better use Color 13 (lighter grey).

