sort key configure widgets either by option name or key name


- Find an algorithm to define the startpositions for drawing of
  Messages, Servermessages, Scorelist and ExtHUD. Goal is to
  minimize overlap while drawing as much info as fits.


- I would like one baseWarningType to have flashing base name
  and flashing time meter, without displaying a shipshape,
  like in 1.3.7.
  The warns displaying a ship (and to a lesser extend a damaged/
  phased/cloaked ship) i find irritating. If I don't look really
  carefull, it seems the ship is already respawned, though the
  countdown is still ticking.

- The new menu stays open if i open it holding down left mousebutton,
  releasing it outside the menu and then return to play.

- The temporary power- and turnspeed meters are deleted and
  their values are now shown numerically in the ExtHUD (as well
  as the packet meters).
  Draw the power and turnspeed values in temporaryMeterColor
  for some seconds if they changed. The delay used for their
  meters in older clients was good, though i don't know
  what value was taken there and if it was hardcoded. About
  3 secs would seem sensible. Though the tempmeter was displayed
  longer, the values can be emphasized shorter if they are
  shown permanent.
  Useful with keySwapSettings on newdarkhell.xp to swap to
  lower power if low on fuel (and having many afterburners),
  to keep the ship controlable.



http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1785690&group_id=147895&atid=769892

- You may like setting oldMessagesColor=0 to make the messages disappear
  fast.  This reveals, that it is no clean/good idea, to use values or
  options in places where they were not intended for -> oldMessagesColor
  is also used for the ExtHUD and for the scorelist headlines.  They
  have nothing in common with old messages in terms of function and
  should therefore have either their own options, or hardcoded colors.

  Maybe make options for normalTextColor, emphasizedTextColor and
  unimportantTextColor.  These could be used more universally (e.g.
  in scorelist, for ExtHUD, for texts in the config window etc.).



- Create a discussion forum for players to state their opinion about
  usefulness/improvements of options, functionality and other issues.
  The need to create an account on sourceforge just to post in the
  available forums is unacceptable to me (i guess it shall prevent
  spamming/flaming).

  Oh, just discovered the tracker on the bp-sf site.  That seems to
  allow anonymous discussion.  Make links on the project web site
  http://bloodspilot.sourceforge.net to the tracker
  http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=147895 and to the
  sf-project http://sourceforge.net/projects/bloodspilot
  and invite people to state their opinion.
  Should be a better place for discussion than doing it in the game,
  that destroys the game.

- Create a reusable text entry widget, that can be used for the
  messagebox and in the config windows.
  Can replace all those number displays with "<" and ">" arrows
  beside, which make it complicated/inprecise to change values.
  The arrows can still remain (for quick small changes).  Could
  also be used in the key config.
  Maybe the current messagebox widget can be adapted to achive
  this.

- For each config editor (General Config, Color Config and
  Key Config) save the topmost option (-number) on exit.
  Next time that config editor is reopened it can immediately
  show the last used page (starting at that saved option).
  Would also work if the window was resized in the meantime
  (which the 4.5.4 client does not do, instead it starts at
  the very first option after a resize).
  Should improve usability (especially with many options or
  small windowsize).

- Make an option to switch the CapsLock key off if the
  messagebox is opened or if the bloodspilot client window
  looses input focus.  Should prevent UNWanted de-/
  capitalization.

